left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 1:29:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please evaluate my Critblade thus far (need advise)</span><hr size=1> I'd say auotrain through 24.  That's how far I autotrained.  True, you can probably wait till 28, it's not that hard, but it's a nice reward for your efforts.  You should have +3 or +4 in axe if you have Njessi's axe.  You probably can't get +3 in crit strike items without twinking.  Otherwise it looks fine.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uthralmcmarrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thral McMarrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 3:10:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> actually..</span><hr size=1> Actually, I got a pair of gloves (forget name) that add +3 to Crit Strike.  However, they are currently blue.  I got a pair of gloves last night that are +1 to crit and are red.  i'm thinking for RvR I might use the +3 to crit gloves even if they are grey to me... heck, if I get seriously hit in the hands, I'm probably going down anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushandray.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shandray</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/02 10:39:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: actually..</span><hr size=1> Restart for BG?  I would say don't your waste your time slogging through the mud of another low assassin for the sake of BG RvR but hey, to each his own if you have the free time. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=veloci>Veloci</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/10/02 2:26:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: actually..</span><hr size=1> I have the same +3 gloves and they are blue as well, I have however noticed that in orange armor my AF is capped without the gloves.  Taking that into account wearing them for RvR is a no brainer <p>Veloci Raptor <br>Shadowblade<br><a href=http://www.www.clan-wolverine.org>Clan Wolverine</a><br>Morgan La Fay<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubroombilda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Broombilda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/02 10:45:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: actually..</span><hr size=1> One easy thing to do in order to see if you really care if the gloves are blue/green/grey.  Notice how much AF you have on the stats page, take off the gloves, check how much AF went down.  An even better test is if you have orange gloves, check out the difference between your grey ones and those.  The first thing you will notice is that gloves contribute very little to effective AF.  IMHO they contribute so little to effective AF that you shouldn't look at the color at all, only at the stats they give you.  The same goes for boots and to a lesser degree, hats.<br><br>Broom <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/15/02 11:53:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cableone.net/truggiero/smxumcard.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: actually..</span><hr size=1> Well to reply to the original topic its a solid template, but sense this is a very late reply, Im sure you have found that out by now. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>With the 24 template you had... you will simply own on the BG. Its almost identical to mine and I had a blast out there. <br>Me and my guildmate are specc'd that way and we just slaughtered out there. Oddly enough, my nights out there with my guildmate were the best times I have had in DAoC thusfar.  <p><img src=http://www.cableone.net/truggiero/xummten.gif></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showPrevMessage?topicID=113.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehous